org.openimaj.video

Class VideoWriter<T extends Image<?,T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.openimaj.video.Video<T>
      • org.openimaj.video.processor.VideoProcessor<T>
        • org.openimaj.video.VideoWriter<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of Image
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Closeable, AutoCloseable, Iterable<T>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    VideoCache, XuggleVideoWriter

    public abstract class VideoWriter<T extends Image<?,T>>
extends VideoProcessor<T>
    An abstract class which classes can override to provide video writing capabilities.

    The addFrame(Image) method must be overridden by implementing subclasses to actually perform the encoding and writing of the video frame.

    The class is an extension of a video processor which allows the writer to act in a processing chain. The implementation of the VideoProcessor interface calls the addFrame(Image) method for every frame that is passed in the processor.

    Author:
    David Dupplaw (dpd@ecs.soton.ac.uk)

      • processFrame

        public T processFrame(T frame)
        Process a frame in this video. The processor must determine itself what is to be done with the frame that is processed. It is suggest that subclass processors add listeners for processed frames if they are required. The implementation must process the frame in-place and the frame should be returned.
